<font color="#FF0000">IS IT WRONG NOT TO TRUST ?</font><br>
<tt>Sun Nov 16 11:38:50 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
SW, you're right, We should trust, but is it wrong not to trust others? I do not know. Is it within our nature to trust others, perhaps, but our own nature tells us also not to. <br><br>
I don’t even trust myself, find it hard to trust others, I do trust God and in God. I always examine my own motives on why I do what I do. Always desire to conduct myself honorably in all things. But, fail to do so often. <br><br>
I find it fascinating when I am entrusted by God with individuals in deep pain, need and compassion. I often wonder if its me or what He has invested in me that does what I do. Who, do I thank for the good in me, who do I complaint to for the bad. There are some people I can trust. Others trust in me, because they know what I stand for, some can’t stand me because I do.<br><br>
I guess just knowing that I do what I do only seeking approval from God is the most important part of my life. It doesn’t matter what others think. Is it wrong not to trust others? <br><br>
I like what the other Paul once said, perhaps it also relate to trust in ourselves, others and in God.<br><br>
“For that which I am doing, I do not understand; for I am not practicing what I {would} like to {do,} but I am doing the very thing I hate.<br>
For I know that nothing good dwells in me, that is, in my flesh; for the wishing is present in me, but the doing of the good {is} not. For the good that I wish, I do not do; but I practice the very evil that I do not wish. <br>
But if I am doing the very thing I do not wish, I am no longer the one doing it, but sin which dwells in me. I find then the principle that evil is present in me, the one who wishes to do good. For I joyfully concur with the law of God in the inner man, but I see a different law in the members of my body, waging war against the law of my mind, and making me a prisoner of the law of sin which is in my members. <br>
Wretched man that I am! Who will set me free from the body of this death?<br>
Thanks be to God through Jesus Christ our Lord! So then, on the one hand I myself with my mind am serving the law of God, but on the other, with my flesh the law of sin. (Romans 7:15, 18-25NAS)<br><br>
Is it wrong not to trust others? I do not know. <br><br>

